{
  "stem": "17821.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 92.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it no longer is the same because what was a marketplace two days a week-- and they brought stalls in and set them up and took them down again-- that was changed to have a more elegant kind of a center.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the marketplace was put somewhere else in the town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a nice town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was about a-- about a, a mile's walk down to the river.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My father, who was a tailor and had his own tailor shop with several men working for him, he worked very hard all the week.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And on Sunday morning-- every Sunday morning, he went-- walked down to the river a mile, along the river a mile and back again home.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was very happy-- once I remembered to go with him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And how pleased he was to have my-- this growing girl interested enough to go with him on his lonely walk.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father didn't-- either my father nor mother had advanced education at all, though they would have benefited by them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I remember for quite a while on Friday nights, even though it was Shabbos, there were some public lectures being given at the local college.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I took my father with me every Friday night.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was quite a close relationship between us, I think.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I've told you that when he had-- gave the five pounds for the money that Dr.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Weizmann was trying to get all over England ready for trying to establish a Jewish state that he had the certificate put in my own name-- in my name.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So I think that really relates that, I guess.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had chicken every Shabbos, OK?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What, what were your parents' names?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was Emma [?",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
